CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1773144737
OL,3,CChampion horse trainer found guilty of
OL,4,Clate-night assault on dog walker
OL,6,FA jury at Cardiff Crown Court took 90
OL,7,Fminutes to find Williams, aged 54,
OL,8,Fguilty of causing grievous bodily harm
OL,9,Fwith intent on Monday, 9 March.
OL,11,FDavid Elias KC, defending, asked for
OL,12,Fthe sentencing hearing to be adjourned
OL,13,Ffor reports and to give Williams time
OL,14,Fto put in place alternative
OL,15,Farrangements for his racing business
OL,16,Fshould he be jailed.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1773144737
OL,3,CChampion horse trainer found guilty of
OL,4,Clate-night assault on dog walker
OL,6,F"In the circumstances of this case,
OL,7,Fbearing in mind he is 54 and of
OL,8,Fhitherto good character, we would
OL,9,Finvite the court to adjourn for a pre-
OL,10,Fsentence report so that this court
OL,11,Fknows everything it needs to about Mr
OL,12,FWilliams," Mr Elias said.
OL,14,F"As I have indicated, Mr Williams
OL,15,Fknows that he is at serious risk of
OL,16,Flosing his liberty and that he asks
OL,17,Ffor bail to be extended.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@JO]vD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1773144737
OL,3,CChampion horse trainer found guilty of
OL,4,Clate-night assault on dog walker
OL,6,F"He has a condition not to contact
OL,7,Fdirectly or indirectly the complainant
OL,8,Fin the case, and there have been no
OL,9,Fdifficulties with that hitherto.
OL,11,F"He has his business and he will need
OL,12,Fto consider how that will be looked
OL,13,Fafter, bearing in mind the risk of him
OL,14,Flosing his liberty.
OL,16,F"He would like some time prior to
OL,17,Fsentence, which he would have if the
OL,18,Fcourt orders a pre-sentence report, to
OL,19,Fput things in place in case it is that
OL,20,Fhe loses his liberty.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/10
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,463,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1773144737
OL,3,CChampion horse trainer found guilty of
OL,4,Clate-night assault on dog walker
OL,6,F"Indeed, he has very pressing
OL,7,Fcommitments in the racing world this
OL,8,Fweek, which he would like to fulfil if
OL,9,Fthat is possible."
OL,11,FRecorder Angharad Price continued
OL,12,FWilliams's conditional bail and said
OL,13,Fhe would be sentenced on April 14
OL,14,Fafter the preparation of reports.
OL,16,F"We will adjourn until April 14 and
OL,17,Funtil then your bail will be enlarged
OL,18,Fon the same terms," she said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@RO]xD@AOUzD@SO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/10
